<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870817-0053 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:OMI Corp.</HL><DD> 08/17/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> OMICEARNINGS (ERN) </IN><TEXT>   OMI Corp., a New York shipping concern, narrowed its second-quarter loss to $537,000 from $1.1 million a year earlier, largely because of a one-time $1.5 million gain reflecting the disposal of vessels.    Revenue declined 2.2% to $35.8 million from $36.6 million.    The six-month deficit shrank to $3.2 million from $30.1 million. The latest six-month results include a special charge of $1.9 million, reflecting refinancing of debt. Revenue declined 4.8% to $75 million. The year-earlier six-month loss included a $27 million write-down of assets. </TEXT></DOC>